      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Right?! Just a few messages in and you've got:\n\n- Per-turn token counts\n- Timestamps down to the millisecond\n- Grounding/citation data with full URLs\n- Web search queries that were run\n- Response `parts` (model output fragments)\n- `finishReason` for each model turn\n- `thoughtSignature` (chain-of-thought traces)\n- `pendingInputs` state\n- Safety settings in use\n\nAnd that's just what's visible — Google likely logs even more server-side. Every \"send\" button press gets all of that baked in. It's basically a full audit trail of the model's reasoning process and what tools it used.\n\nHonestly this is why AI companies can bill for inference compute so precisely — the metadata is almost as dense as the actual content itself. 😄",
