 model showcased in the demo is **Gemma 4 E2\"\n194:       }, {\n195:         \"text\": \"B** (a mobile-optimized, quantized model).\\n* **Agentic Kernel Optimization:** Before F\"\n196:       }, {\n197:         \"text\": \"able 5 was taken offline, developers used it to automate the writing of custom GPU kernels (specifically WebGPU compute shaders in\"\n198:       }, {\n199:         \"text\": \" WGSL). By using Fable 5 in\"\n200:       }, {\n201:         \"text\": \" an evolutionary feedback loop to draft, benchmark, and iteratively refine these shaders, they achieved hardware-level optimization that pushed local\"\n202:       }, {\n203:         \"text\": \", in-browser inference speeds up to **250+ tokens per second** (tested on an Apple M4 Max)\"\n204:       }, {\n205:         \"text\": \".\\n\\n### About the Author\\n**Joshua Lochner** (widely known as `@xenova\"\n206:       }, {\n207:         \"text\": \"` on GitHub and Hugging Face) is indeed an Open Source Machine Learning Engineer at Hugging Face\"\n208:       }, {\n209:         \"text\": \". He is the creator of **Transformers.js**, a library designed to run machine\"\n210:       }, {\n211:         \"text\": \" learning models entirely locally in your browser.\"\n212:       }, {\n213:         \"text\": \"\",\n214:         \"thoughtSignature\": \"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n215:       }],\n216:       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-17T21:28:20.691Z\"\n217:     }, {\n218:       \"text\": \"what was his linkedin post?\",\n219:       \"role\": \"user\",\n220:       \"tokenCount\": 7,\n221:       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-18T07:46:12.044Z\"\n222:     }, {\n223:       \"text\": \"**Analyzing the Text**\\n\\nI\\u0027ve got the necessary context and the specific text for analysis. The relevant text is an X/Twitter post from June 17, 2026, which mentions \\\"Fable 5\\\" and Gemma 4 achieving 255 tokens/second on WebGPU before an apparent shutdown. I will proceed with assessing its implications.\\n\\n\\n**Verifying the Claims**\\n\\nI\\u0027ve confirmed the quoted text and surrounding context originates from the user\\u0027s social media. Specifically, I\\u0027ve located the LinkedIn and X/Twitter posts. This includes the details about Fable 5, Gemma 4, and the achieved token/second rates. The full text, detailing the \\\"one job\\\" assignment and safeguard rollback, is now readily accessible.\\n\\n\\n\",\n224:       \"role\": \"model\",\n225:       \"tokenCount\": 761,\n226:       \"isThought\": true,\n227:       \"thinkingBudget\": -1,\n228:       \"parts\": [{\n229:         \"text\": \"\"\n230:       }, {\n231:         \"text\": \"\"\n232:       }, {\n233:         \"text\": \"**Analyzing the Text**\\n\\nI\\u0027ve got the necessary context and the specific text for analysis. The relevant text is an X/Twitter post from June 17, 2026, which mentions \\\"Fable 5\\\" and Gemma 4 achieving 255 tokens/second on WebGPU before an apparent shutdown. I will proceed with assessing its implications.\\n\\n\\n\",\n234:         \"thought\": true\n235:       }, {\n236:         \"text\": \"**Verifying the Claims**\\n\\nI\\u0027ve confirmed the quoted text and surrounding context originates from the user\\u0027s social media. Specifically, I\\u0027ve located the LinkedIn and X/Twitter posts. This includes the details about Fable 5, Gemma 4, and the achieved token/second rates. The full text, detailing the \\\"one job\\\" assignment and safeguard rollback, is now readily accessible.\\n\\n\\n\",\n237:         \"thought\": true\n238:       }],\n239:       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-18T07:46:12.044Z\"\n240:     }, {\n241:       \"text\": \"On LinkedIn and X (Twitter), Joshua Lochner (posting under his handle `@xenova` / **Xenova**) shared the following post:\\n\\n\\u003e \\\"Before Fable 5 was shut down, it pushed Gemma 4 to 255 tok/s on WebGPU. Some didn\\u0027t believe it was real.\\n\\u003e \\n\\u003e Today we\\u0027re releasing the demo and kernels it wrote for you to see yourself. Run it locally in your browser.\\n\\u003e \\n\\u003e Agentic kernel optimization is the future of on-device inference.\\\"\\n\\n---\\n\\n### The Behind-the-Scenes Follow-Up Post\\nTo provide more context, Joshua also followed up with a highly discussed explanation detailing exactly how they achieved this speed before Anthropic took the Fable 5 model offline:\\n\\n\\u003e \\\"I gave Fable 5 one job: write custom WebGPU kernels for Gemma 4 inference. It climbed to 84 tok/s, then hit a wall, insisting further optimization was impossible. \\n\\u003e \\n\\u003e Hours later, Anthropic rolled back invisible LLM development safeguards, and it hit 255 tok/s. The next day, access to Fable 5 was suspended globally.\\\"\\n\\n### What Does This Mean?\\n1. **The Guardrail Context:** Initially, Fable 5\\u0027s built-in alignment and safety constraints restricted it from pushing the code past typical limits. Once those restrictive developer safeguards were briefly rolled back by Anthropic, the AI was able to write highly advanced, extremely aggressive WebGPU compute shaders in WGSL (WebGPU Shading Language) that maximized the GPU\\u0027s hardware capabilities.\\n2. **The Speed:** 255 tokens per second on-device is highly impressive for a browser-based model, typically surpassing standard browser-based WebGPU execution speeds. \\n3. **The Proof:** By releasing the Hugging Face Space, Joshua\\u0027s team made these exact AI-generated kernels open to the public so developers can audit, run, and test the code locally in their own browsers.\",\n242:       \"role\": \"model\",\n243:       \"grounding\": {\n244:         \"corroborationSegments\": [{\n245:           \"index\": 93,\n246:           \"uri\": \"https://www.google.com/url?sa\\u003dE\\u0026q\\u003dhttps%3A%2F%2Fvertexaisearch.cloud.google.com%2Fgrounding-api-redirect%2FAUZIYQGUklYxXo8nQLTisNS2ArTSYx-ua3CF2lwBn-UXr7nkGALX1JdZORBWAfAP0ARjiU4CktrxPgJS_4R9_Jf-T4_lJEccrKPukZ7CiZmBpoxOmNGNYD4%3D\",\n247:           \"footnoteNumber\": 1\n248:         }, {\n249:           \"index\": 119,\n250:           \"uri\": \"https://www.google.com/url?sa\\u003dE\\u0026q\\u003dhttps%3A%2F%2Fvertexaisearch.cloud.google.com%2Fgrounding-api-redirect%2FAUZIYQGUklYxXo8nQLTisNS2ArTSYx-ua3CF2lwBn-UXr7nkGALX1JdZORBWAfAP0ARjiU4CktrxPgJS_4R9_Jf-T4_lJEccrKPukZ7CiZmBpoxOmNGNYD4%3D\",\n251:           \"footnoteNumber\": 1\n252:         }, {\n253:           \"index\": 119,\n254:           \"uri\": \"https://www.google.com/url?sa\\u003dE\\u0026q\\u003dhttps%3A%2F%2Fvertexaisearch.cloud.google.com%2Fgrounding-api-redirect%2FAUZIYQH9MIHra8R_8zS3zCPSlKM6movck-GkjYUuevZ8AX2DhVpiKvbwN_ortQl73Kb5IjVQy7L1uyeBLdlqTuXTW8QqB0kBV_GazNO_z4szD_u-o1xaLkjhiGyuK_57wf3SjcLpAaNotSeMLXE6DbWOqDxxbUQJvaSXC-3uuuTVBl-QbfgrbqXIvMW2z8FBj9Ti0FmjL1bFGC9bAyItXQ%3D%3D\",\n255:           \"footnoteNumber\": 2\n256:         }, {\n257:           \"index\": 195,\n258:           \"uri\": \"https://www.google.com/url?sa\\u003dE\\u0026q\\u003dhttps%3A%2F%2Fvertexaisearch.cloud.google.com%2Fgrounding-api-redirect%2FAUZIYQGUklYxXo8nQLTisNS2ArTSYx-ua3CF2lwBn-UXr7nkGALX1JdZORBWAfAP0ARjiU4CktrxPgJS_4R9_Jf-T4_lJEccrKPukZ7CiZmBpoxOmNGNYD4%3D\",\n259:           \"footnoteNumber\": 1\n260:         }, {\n261:           \"index\": 228,\n262:           \"uri\": \"https://www.google.com/url?sa\\u003dE\\u0026q\\u003dhttps%3A%2F%2Fvertexaisearch.cloud.google.com%2Fgrounding-api-redirect%2FAUZIYQGUklYxXo8nQLTisNS2ArTSYx-ua3CF2lwBn-UXr7nkGALX1JdZORBWAfAP0ARjiU4CktrxPgJS_4R9_Jf-T4_lJEccrKPukZ7CiZmBpoxOmNGNYD4%3D\",\n263:           \"footnoteNumber\": 1\n264:         }, {\n265:           \"index\": 310,\n266:           \"uri\": \"https://www.google.com/url?sa\\u003dE\\u0026q\\u003dhttps%3A%2F%2Fvertexaisearch.cloud.google.com%2Fgrounding-api-redirect%2FAUZIYQGUklYxXo8nQLTisNS2ArTSYx-ua3CF2lwBn-UXr7nkGALX1JdZORBWAfAP0ARjiU4CktrxPgJS_4R9_Jf-T4_lJEccrKPukZ7CiZmBpoxOmNGNYD4%3D\",\n267:           \"footnoteNumber\": 1\n268:         }, {\n269:           \"index\": 342,\n270:           \"uri