    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"mavis session export --help 2>&1\", \"description\": \"Check mavis export command\"}",
      "output": "Usage: mavis session [options] [command]\n\nManage agent sessions. For users and external apps only — Mavis and its agents\nmust NOT invoke session commands directly; dispatch via mavis-team plan.\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help                          display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  list|ls [options] [agentId]         List sessions for an agent (defaults to\n                                      active agent)\n  info [options] <sessionId>          Show detailed information about a session\n  update [options] <sessionId>        Update session title or workspace\n                                      directory\n  abort <sessionId>                   Abort a running session\n  messages|msg [options] <sessionId>  Show message history for a session\n  compress <sessionId>                Archive a session (hidden from list,\n                                      reversible)\n  diff [options] <sessionId>          Show file changes for a session\n  close <sessionId>                   Permanently delete a session\n                                      (irreversible). Use compress to archive\n                                      reversibly.\n  rotate [options]                    Rotate the current session — archives the\n                                      old session and creates a fresh one with\n                                      a handoff prompt\n  new [options] <agent>               Create a new session for an agent and\n                                      send an initial prompt. Use --from root\n                                      for a standalone session, or --from\n                                      <sessionId> for a child session (spawn).\n                                      For users and external apps only — Mavis\n                                      and its agents must NOT invoke this;\n                                      dispatch via mavis-team plan.\n  scratchpad                          Inspect or open the root scratchpad of a\n                                      session tree\n                                      (<dataDir>/scratchpads/<rootSessionId>/scratchpad.md)\n  help [command]                      display help for command\n\nTo send messages between sessions, use `mavis communication`.\n",
