    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "There's no `export` command. But I can use `mavis session messages` to get the conversation and format it. The session messages are fetched from the API, not from the local SQLite. Let me now write a script to fetch all messages and save them as a clean JSON/Markdown file.\n\nActually, looking at the mavis session messages output, it has a `nextCursor` field, meaning there are more messages. The full output was truncated. Let me now write a Node.js script that:\n1. Queries all messages from this session using the mavis CLI\n2. Formats them as a clean export file\n\nBut actually, I should just run the mavis session messages command and save it to a file, then parse it.",
      "timestamp": 1781848346143
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "write",
      "code": "{\"content\": \"// Mavis Session Exporter\\n// Usage: node export-session.js <session-id> [output-file]\\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\\nconst fs = require('fs');\\nconst path = require('path');\\n\\nconst sessionId = process.argv[2] || 'mvs_54b5193807c44930852f615d9ba50aad';\\nconst outputFile = process.argv[3] || `session-export-${sessionId}.json`;\\n\\nconsole.log(`Exporting session: ${sessionId}`);\\n\\n// Fetch all messages using mavis CLI\\nlet allMessages = [];\\nlet cursor = null;\\nlet page = 1;\\n\\ndo {\\n  const cursorArg = cursor ? `--cursor ${cursor}` : '';\\n  const cmd = `mavis session messages ${sessionId} ${cursorArg}`;\\n  console.log(`  Page ${page}...`);\\n  const raw = execSync(cmd, { encoding: 'utf8', maxBuffer: 50 * 1024 * 1024 });\\n  const parsed = JSON.parse(raw);\\n  allMessages.push(...parsed.messages);\\n  cursor = parsed.nextCursor;\\n  page++;\\n} while (cursor);\\n\\nconsole.log(`Total messages: ${allMessages.length}`);\\n\\n// Extract clean conversation (strip tool call internals for readability)\\nconst conversation = allMessages\\n  .filter(m => m.role === 'user' || m.role === 'assistant')\\n  .map(m => ({\\n    msg_id: m.msg_id,\\n    role: m.role,\\n    timestamp: new Date(m.timestamp).toISOString(),\\n    content: m.msg_content || m.thinking_content || '',\\n    thinking: m.thinking_content && m.msg_content ? m.thinking_content : undefined,\\n    finish_reason: m.finish_reason,\\n    usage: m.usage,\\n    source: m.source,\\n  }));\\n\\n// Save as JSON\\nfs.writeFileSync(outputFile, JSON.stringify({\\n  sessionId,\\n  exportedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\\n  totalMessages: allMessages.length,\\n  messages: conversation,\\n}, null, 2));\\n\\nconsole.log(`Saved to: ${outputFile}`);\\n\", \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\export-session.js\"}",
      "output": "Wrote file successfully.\n\n<system-reminder>\nYou just created or modified a file. If this file IS the deliverable the user asked for (document, report, image, spreadsheet, archive, audio, video, code artifact, etc.), you MUST include it in your response with `<media src=\"/absolute/path\" />`; do not only print the path. If it is only an intermediate/source edit, no media tag is needed.\n</system-reminder>",
