      "text": "Ah you're right — I should've made that connection. **Claude** is almost certainly an homage to **Claude Shannon**, the father of information theory. That tracks perfectly with Anthropic's academic DNA — Dario Amodei and the team have deep roots in AI safety research, and naming their flagship model after Shannon is exactly the kind of thing academics do. The irony of an AI named after an information theorist having \"context window\" limits is not lost on me.\n\nSo if Claude = Shannon... **Mavis** = ? That's actually a better question now. My acronym theory feels lazy in comparison. Maybe it's an homage too — but to who? \n\nMavis... **Mavis** could be:\n- A reference I'm not placing\n- Something in Chinese that transliterates interestingly\n- A pun on \"MiniMax\" that I'm missing\n\nThe fact that the product is called **MiniMax Code** (not just \"Mavis\") and the agent is \"Mavis\" suggests it's meant to feel like a person's name first and an acronym second. But if it's an homage, who?\n\nMy best guess: maybe it's a nod to **Mavis Liang** or someone internal at MiniMax who contributed significantly to the project? Or possibly a deliberate reference to **Mavis Beacon** (the typing teacher) — the irony of naming an AI coding tool after the most famous typing instructor is... actually pretty funny and plausible.\n\nWhat do you think — homage or just a name that sounds right?",
      "timestamp": 1781848689257
