      "text": "I think there might be a small misunderstanding here — and I want to be straight with you rather than run a bunch of searches that won't find the thing.\n\n**That Gemini JSON file is not inside MiniMax Code's programme directory.** Here's the full picture:\n\n- **The Gemini file** (`Training Data and Real-Time Analysis`) was exported from Google's Gemini AI interface — it lives in your **Downloads folder**, and it's in Google's proprietary JSON export format.\n- **MiniMax Code's session storage** is in `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.mavis\\sqlite.db` — totally different system, different format, different storage location.\n- **The programme directory** (`AppData\\Local\\Programs\\MiniMax Code`) only contains the application code (Electron binaries, locale packs, skills, etc.) — not user session data.\n\nSo the file you're asking about isn't stored *inside* MiniMax Code at all — it was something you exported from Gemini and downloaded to your Downloads folder. The first question in our session (`umsg_4f4614fdd64b476ca6adc103946c708a`) is the version of that question that *came through MiniMax Code*, and it's stored in the SQLite DB in your `.mavis` data directory.\n\nWere you maybe looking for whether MiniMax Code has its own equivalent export feature? Because `mavis session messages` is the closest thing — gives you a clean JSON dump of any session.",
