verything. The most likely explanation is that the session was created at 05:43 but sat idle for 6 minutes before any actual conversation happened, and at some point the topic shifted to Windows File Paths, which is what generated the title.\n\nThough I'm now wondering if the user might be conflating the session title with an actual message — maybe \"Windows File Path Explanation\" was never a message at all, just the auto-generated title from the MiniMax Code UI based on what the conversation was actually about. The user is absolutely certain that their first message was \"Windows File Path Explanation,\" so it's probably not a confusion. Since there's no other session from today and the export captures the entire conversation from 05:49 onwards, that message must have existed but isn't in the database anymore — possibly due to a session rotation or restart that cleared it.",
