    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "So neither sqlite.db nor nexus.db contains the session ID `mvs_54b5193807c44930852f615d9ba50aad`. The session data must be stored elsewhere or retrieved from a remote API.\n\nThe `mavis session list` command is returning session data, so where is it coming from? It could be from a MiniMax remote server since MiniMax Code connects to their cloud API.\n\nBut the messages ARE in sqlite.db (we found them earlier via `mavis session messages`). So the session metadata and messages are stored differently:\n- Session list/metadata: likely from MiniMax cloud API\n- Session messages: stored locally in sqlite.db\n\n\n- \nThe gap between session creation and the first stored message might mean messages are written to sqlite.db asynchronously or buffered, or the session metadata lives server-side while the messages are stored locally but haven't been persisted yet for this session.\n\nLet me try fetching more messages from the API using a higher limit to see if earlier messages are cached there.",
